Notebook[{
Cell["Visualization Tutorial", "Title",ExpressionUUID->"0586b97d-d527-40c4-99b3-212aacffdee3"],

Cell["\<\
A walkthrough of the three pieces of the visualization layer: diffuse \
rendering with InfraSceneHighlight, the declarative scene language built on \
InfraScene, and the Manipulate-based viewers. All three converge on the same \
head dispatch and the same opacity/thickness envelope.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"3e52e41a-4f62-42d1-b45a-1abc809b2f4d"],

Cell["Setup", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"5d6b4072-594d-4eb5-930f-72f366665d64"],

Cell["Needs[\"WolframInstitute`SyntheticInfrageometry`\"]", "Code",ExpressionUUID->"2c62449e-ec4f-4217-b40b-e1c49eb98377"],

Cell["Define a working graph used throughout this tutorial.", "CodeText",ExpressionUUID->"45d4fe44-e4d9-40e5-bb3e-46c699e85b82"],

Cell["g = GridGraph[{4, 4}]", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"9765104e-5367-47b1-9c09-5955d374d664"],

Cell["Diffuse rendering of a single multi-object", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"9935cd6d-15c2-4b55-b2a7-6ef8b4e57f66"],

Cell["\<\
Find* functions return wrapped multi-realisation objects. Pipe one straight \
into InfraSceneHighlight to see every realisation diffuse-rendered.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"0dcb609f-b8e4-43ad-b56d-41d43b6bfcfe"],

Cell["\<\
Every shortest path between corner 1 and corner 16, drawn together with \
within-object multiplicity reflected in opacity:\
\>", "CodeText",ExpressionUUID->"06564e24-cc25-4db4-b686-423263b44bc4"],

Cell["InfraSceneHighlight[g, {FindSegment[g, 1, 16, All]}]", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"258f9d50-2820-4a47-bda1-ce28a1a7ea9c"],

Cell["\<\
Vertices and edges that participate in many realisations get higher opacity. \
Edges that participate in only one realisation get the minimum opacity.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"cbdcd69c-e6d4-47c7-be2c-710c660ab064"],

Cell["Multiple objects, default palette", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"c98e2a77-4050-4f91-a4f9-3ece00b78ec5"],

Cell["\<\
Pass several wrapped objects in one list. The palette assigns a default \
colour by head.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"bb29ad56-478f-4ce0-b8b1-4b3ececa28f4"],

Cell["\<\
InfraSceneHighlight[g, {FindSegment[g, 1, 16, All], FindShell[g, 6, 2, All], \
FindCircle[g, 6, 2, All]}]\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"4c66ec62-6216-4bae-9187-20df294d9767"],

Cell["\<\
The segment is the InfraSegmentColor (warm orange), the shell is the \
InfraShellColor (sage), the circle is the InfraCircleColor (teal).\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"5239b4a6-f6ae-4c22-859e-0af0314b71cd"],

Cell["Per-object colour override", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"e5d503b8-c767-4df9-879c-78b74d77cd31"],

Cell["Wrap an entry as `obj -> colour` to override the default.", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"3a706fbb-8cc1-44cf-aa06-9051981e0fc4"],

Cell["\<\
InfraSceneHighlight[g, {FindSegment[g, 1, 16, All] -> Red, FindShell[g, 6, 2, \
All] -> Blue}]\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"506cd741-1c50-45bd-abf5-4c741c9cb003"],

Cell["Tuning the diffusion envelope", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"682e1e33-d399-414d-8486-477f236454eb"],

Cell["\<\
The diffuse rendering scales opacity, edge thickness, and point size across \
the within-object multiplicity. Tune the ranges via options.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"4cc4e9d8-176c-430e-9392-0134ef45844f"],

Cell["\<\
InfraSceneHighlight[g, {FindSegment[g, 1, 16, All]}, \"OpacityRange\" -> \
{0.1, 1.0}, \"ThicknessRange\" -> {0.5, 8.0}]\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"63237738-8cce-4a99-91b5-411c87fea645"],

Cell["Mixing projective and Euclidean objects", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"6b1fde67-d0e8-447e-90f4-7b2174376ac4"],

Cell["\<\
The projective wrappers InfraRay and InfraPencil dispatch to the same Paths \
renderer. The pencil's apex naturally gets visual emphasis from \
count-weighting because it appears in every constituent ray.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"d518589e-a7d2-484e-aeb1-fca87d018a2c"],

Cell["\<\
InfraSceneHighlight[g, {FindPencil[g, 6] -> Red, InfraPoint[{6}] -> Black}]\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"83025ea2-30fb-4b91-b02d-3de33b106ba1"],

Cell["Declarative scenes", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"c8a5c915-f8d0-4cf5-87cf-e8be479ad42b"],

Cell["\<\
InfraScene lets you describe a configuration symbolically. The scene engine \
evaluates every step on a given graph and returns a list of branches.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"e939524d-3268-4a3b-8166-073c13dea25d"],

Cell["\<\
A two-point bisector scene: pick two endpoints, then take their bisecting \
hyperplane.\
\>", "CodeText",ExpressionUUID->"647a46e3-39b9-4230-8237-4917c85047de"],

Cell["\<\
scene = InfraScene[{p1, p2, h}, {p1 == InfraPoint[1], p2 == InfraPoint[16], h \
== InfraPlane[p1, p2]}]\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"a2a6b2c1-c7e1-4161-8e31-c4e5c2348353"],

Cell["Evaluate on the grid:", "CodeText",ExpressionUUID->"2dedf0ae-a349-4d2e-be0a-9efd394007a8"],

Cell["instances = FindInfraScene[scene, g]", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"6f960268-913e-42de-bfe7-3fbbc0633a33"],

Cell["Read out one instance:", "CodeText",ExpressionUUID->"08f13659-ab0a-418f-b52f-e5e7991e3c76"],

Cell["First[instances][[1]][h]", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"552c40fb-0011-4e4f-916a-e2bbfaf0513c"],

Cell["Visualizing a scene", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"bdf56a12-66ac-41f5-8e11-b91a1e665103"],

Cell["\<\
The interactive InfraSceneViewer wraps the same scene in a step-aware UI: \
navigate by step, fix-and-advance to pin a binding and proceed, reset to \
clear all fixed bindings.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"3f45e059-bd5d-433a-a232-d961ebd8c037"],

Cell["InfraSceneViewer[scene, g]", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"a74f1a80-7730-43a9-abbf-2566066c007b"],

Cell["A scene assertion", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"6feace92-aea4-4b47-b616-918476801989"],

Cell["\<\
Assertions test predicates with current bindings substituted. They are \
written using the Infra*Q heads (InfraSegmentQ, InfraLineQ, InfraShellQ, \
InfraPlaneQ, InfraCircleQ, InfraParallelQ, InfraIntersectQ).\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"8c103dbc-87e7-4b17-a11d-57417323502c"],

Cell["Build a scene that asserts two segments are parallel:", "CodeText",ExpressionUUID->"47610102-a12f-441b-b8c4-1ffae1aa1ee3"],

Cell["\<\
sceneParallel = InfraScene[{a, b, c, d, l1, l2}, {a == InfraPoint[1], b == \
InfraPoint[5], c == InfraPoint[2], d == InfraPoint[6], l1 == InfraLine[a, b], \
l2 == InfraLine[c, d], InfraParallelQ[l1, l2]}]\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"294cd446-d717-44ad-9b14-3920c4336d28"],

Cell["FindInfraScene[sceneParallel, g] // Length", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"5161b8b2-c328-4985-b3ea-03392e7ad627"],

Cell["Per-primitive viewers", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"d49a25d1-338e-498f-8f29-067ca389eb63"],

Cell["\<\
Each viewer is a thin Manipulate over the corresponding Find*. Drag sliders, \
change setter bars, and watch the diffuse rendering update live.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"c226dc54-06cf-46b2-83f1-4bcef21b8252"],

Cell["\<\
PointViewer[g] -- pick points by source (Random / Center / Periphery), \
separation, count.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"24c660f9-dc2d-4ba0-bd2f-1d903cdd7579"],

Cell["\<\
SegmentViewer[g] -- two endpoints + path-space selector + count cap.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"61dd81bf-9560-410c-9dad-1b6ed57628de"],

Cell["\<\
ShellViewer[g] -- center + radius + Method (Metric / Separating).\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"22c04ba5-017c-411d-911f-d42831b02d99"],

Cell["CircleViewer[g] -- center + radius + path-space selector.", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"7a4011d6-2db7-48c9-977a-bf83797e1c0d"],

Cell["SegmentViewer[g]", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"5ed8407a-5174-4399-b302-4a83199507bc"],

Cell["Cooperating multi-objects", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"c9b3099a-d519-416a-bbf1-288370b115dc"],

Cell["\<\
Many objects in one call let you read off composite invariants visually.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"5a6207b0-bc4c-4ae7-9f81-dfba7091a156"],

Cell["\<\
Equilateral triangle on segment 1-3 of a small grid: shell at distance 2 from \
each endpoint, intersected.\
\>", "CodeText",ExpressionUUID->"381f5d1e-a04d-48ef-b801-566f1bf652d7"],

Cell["smallGrid = GridGraph[{4, 4}]", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"0b973bf3-7352-4ceb-9832-6e6ae8a92518"],

Cell["\<\
InfraSceneHighlight[smallGrid, {FindSegment[smallGrid, 1, 3, All] -> Black, \
FindShell[smallGrid, 1, 2, All] -> Red, FindShell[smallGrid, 3, 2, All] -> \
Blue, CompleteEquilateralTriangle[smallGrid, 1, 3, All] -> Green}]\
\>", "Input",ExpressionUUID->"5c415547-4255-4709-a032-fdd206f2fe74"],

Cell["\<\
The two shells overlap on every apex of an equilateral triangle on (1, 3); \
the green points highlight those apex vertices.\
\>", "Text",ExpressionUUID->"d3d63fdd-fbcd-4b14-a35b-ba9a8d354e9d"],

Cell["See also", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"f57bc4ad-5bdc-40fd-9538-52b8c77ca6b7"],

Cell["\<\
VisualizationGuide -- categorical overview of every symbol in the layer.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"29f0dbc5-1b96-4b8f-ba36-782d5376adc1"],

Cell["\<\
EuclideanLayerTutorial -- the Find* family used as input to the rendering \
pipeline.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"9ba1d630-4d3d-4dbd-a65f-6f6fbcf4226c"],

Cell["\<\
ProjectiveLayerTutorial -- multi-CONSTITUENT pencil rendering with apex \
emphasis.\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"0955e929-b23d-4f14-aff6-3f3760103129"],

Cell["References", "Section",ExpressionUUID->"72dc702d-698d-4591-badd-6ee4cd9f0a3a"],

Cell["\<\
Wolfram, GeometricScene system reference, \
https://reference.wolfram.com/language/ref/GeometricScene.html\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"e356ea5f-291a-424c-ac9e-3ef3406cc073"],

Cell["\<\
Wolfram, HighlightGraph reference, \
https://reference.wolfram.com/language/ref/HighlightGraph.html (the \
underlying Wolfram primitive that InfraSceneHighlight dispatches to).\
\>", "Item",ExpressionUUID->"3693d171-9c2a-4538-9ae2-50fef11b824a"]
},
FrontEndVersion->"14.3 for Mac OS X ARM (64-bit) (July 8, 2025)",
